===Alternative spellings===
*[[assagai]]
*[[assagaie]], [[assagay]], [[assegay]], [[azagaia]], [[hassagay]], [[hassaguay]], [[zagaie]], [[zagaye]] (''obsolete'')
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'æsəgaɪ/
===Etymology===
From French [[azagaie]] (now [[zagaie]]) or Portuguese [[azagaia]], Spanish [[azagaya]], from colloquial Arabic [[زفاية]] + [[ال]], from Berber ''zaġāya'' ‘spear’.
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A slim hardwood [[spear]] with an iron tip, especially those used by [[Bantu]] peoples.
#:*'''1922''': A birdchief, bluestreaked and feathered in war panoply with his '''assegai''', striding through a crackling canebrake over beechmast and acorns.  (Joyce, ''Ulysses'')
# The tree from which assegai spears are made, ''Curtisia dentata''.
===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To [[spear]] with an assegai.
